You can use `row_number()` and `join`:

    select a.result, b.result
    from (select a.*, row_number() over (order by ?) as seqnum
          from &lt;a&gt;
         ) a join
         (select b.*, row_number() over (order by ?) as seqnum
          from &lt;b&gt;
         ) b
         on a.seqnum = b.seqnum
    order by a.seqnum;

The `?` is for the ordering of each of the result sets.  `&lt;a&gt;` and `&lt;b&gt;` are for whatever query you are using.

