answers.body_markdown:
Your `useEffect` is only being called after your component has been mounted, because you passed `[]` in the second argument. If you want to have a side effect based on some state you should something like this:

```
useEffect(() =&gt; {
    let interval = null;
    if (redirect) {  
       setRedirect(false);
       interval = setInterval(() =&gt; {
          // Redirect to another page
       }, 1000);
    }
    return () =&gt; interval ? clearInterval(interval) : null;
  }, [redirect])
```

Passing the property that you want to have a side effect on is what you have to do. https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-effect.html

